item.title: If someone can help me add G.E to eclipse 639 i will give you a mega reward!
item.dc:creator: @EclipseRSPS EclipseRSPS
item.description:
@EclipseRSPS wrote:

You would need to load a higher revision cache, and aquire the proper mapdata, as shown here.

Which is NOT by any means any easy thing to do.

The process and understanding of loading a higher cache -

When a user wants to load higher, the first thing they would need to do is find/develop their own Cache Editor compatible with the version(s) of cache(s) they are attempting to “unpack”.

More popular Cache Editor’s are some developed by Dragonkk or Tom’s Cache Suite, Because they help you SEE the cache with images and maps and such, they are really good tools for cache editing.

The entire time you would still be using the original (in the case the 639) client, you will only be editing it to format correctly with the client, you would have to do some server sided conversion as well.

All you are doing is removing the things from the higher cache that you want, and replacing them in the original cache. Then you STILL have to repack it PROPERLY and dump mapdata XD

If you can figure out and do this on your own, more power to you <3

Also I wouldn’t recommend trying to buy help on here, it will get you no where. And you will meet lots of scammers too.

To be honest, I would just update your revision, it is the easiest way <3

[size=18pt]EDIT:[/size]
Disregaurd that entire post ^ :fp:

While writing that I was thinking you wanted NEW Revision RS G.E lol…
What a waste of time ;D
